		<abstract>
			<para>
				MobilityDB is an extension to the <link xl:href="https://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</link> database system and its spatial extension <link xl:href="http://postgis.net/">PostGIS</link>. It allows temporal and spatio-temporal objects to be stored in the database, that is, objects whose attribute values and/or location evolves in time. MobilityDB includes functions for analysis and processing of temporal and spatio-temporal objects and provides support for GiST and SP-GiST indexes. MobilityDB is open source and its code is available on <link xl:href="https://github.com/MobilityDB/MobilityDB">Github</link>. A binding for the Python programming language is also available on <link xl:href="https://github.com/MobilityDB/PyMEOS">Github</link>.
			</para>

			<para>
				<inlinemediaobject xmlns='http://docbook.org/docbook-ng'>
